Class Data

java.lang.Object
java.util.AbstractMap<String,Object>
java.util.HashMap<String,Object>
webfx.devs.Data
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, Map<String,Object>
public class Data extends HashMap<String,Object>
The Data class is an extension of a HashMap<String, Object> and so all HashMap operations can be performed on it. It can work alongside the DataManager to easily store data and efficiently reteieve it.

  • Method Details

    • get

      public <T> T get(String key, Class<T> type)
      Retrieves a value from the Data object and attempts to cast/convert it to the specified type. This can be used as a safe alternative to casting the desired type on data.

      The safest ways of accessing data in a Data object for types other than string, are through this method and typecasting after ensuring DataManager's validateData() is not null.

      Type Parameters:
      T - the generic type
      Parameters:
      key - The key in the Data object.
      type - The Class object of the type to convert to.
      Returns:
      The converted value of type T, null if conversion fails.

    • find

      public Object find(String key)
      Finds a specific value within a Data object, given a key which represents a path to that value

      Example Key: "object1.object2.list[0].value"

      Only objects and lists should be followed by ".", with the desired value following the final "."

      When looking for specific values within lists, the location of that value should be enclosed [] and follow the list's name, e.g. myList[loc]

      Parameters:
      key - The location of the value within the Data object.
      Returns:
      The desired value as an Object

    • getListAsString

      public ArrayList<String> getListAsString(String key)
      Accepts a key from the Data object being used to call this method and returns an ArrayList if applicable.

      The ArrayList will contain type: String

      This method expects the key's value to be of the form: "[val, val, val]"

      Parameters:
      key - The key corresponding the desired data
      Returns:
      An ArrayList<String> of the Data's content for the specified key, or null

    • getIterator

      public Iterator<Object> getIterator()
      Create an Iterator from Data. The Iterator accesses all the immediate values to this Data object.
      Returns:
      A Iterator<Object> of each value in the data object
